reviews.text: Don't let them fool ya. The all you can eat spugotti is boss. One plate you're stuffed

Found this little place in the heart of Shelbyville. Staff was good food was also good. The staff is very helpful and will give you an honest opinion on food choices. They had outdoor tables and a good bourbon selection.

We stayed nearby for a couple of days and this little place was recommended by the hotel staff. There was no front signage which made it harder to find than it should have been, but glad we did as the pizza and spaghetti meals we had were really lovely and very well priced. Server was lovely too and was exceptional.
I enjoy their sausage pizza with nacho cheese sauce for dipping, not much else. My son likes their truffle chicken pizza and taco pizza.
Pizza is phenomenal in my opinion...I only get to eat here when I'm on the road...Twice in the last 15 yrs, but so worth it üëçüëçüëç

detailedReviews.author: Eric Ramsey
detailedReviews.text: I grew up on JB's Pizza King that was on 135 in Greenwood next to at that time True Value. Early 80s and until I graduated in 87 and left for the military. I came home in 2012 and it was gone and then someone opened one in Whiteland and I'm glad it closed because they crucified everything I remember pizza king being. Then an Arnie's restaurant opened up on 135 and they said it was from the Original pizza king Bros. And it was good but not what I remembered. Until tonight. Cagneys is what I remember as a kid. The memories I thought forever gone of the pizza king pizza with my mom and dad had been located. Thank you Cagneys. Not was is delicious but I actually had a moment that got to me from those memories. Fantastic pizza. You will not be disappointed. Thank you so much Cagneys!
